In addition to any other license required by law, a person shall be licensed by the Administration before the person may provide the following services to an individual with developmental disability or a recipient of individual support services:
Day habilitation services;
Residential services;
Services coordination;
Vocational services;
More than 1 family support service, as defined under § 7-701 of this title;
More than 1 individual support service; and
More than 1 community supported living arrangements service.
